THE ALARM start here when they leave the room. THEY BEAT THE CENTURION. NOW THE REAL FIGHT BEGINS. 
This is the crucial transition from the quiet victory of the boss fight into the chaotic terror of the escape. We need to seamlessly stitch Kyboh's personal consequence (if he fails) directly into the dungeon-wide alarm.
Here is the revised and finalized sequence, built with the updated understandings of Tonal Architecture, Kyboh's specific bone enchantments, and the mechanical reality of the world.

THE PIVOT: THE DEMON CORE & THE ALARM
Location: The Centurion Workshop.
Context: The Centurion Prime is dead. Varon has just extracted the Aetherial Matrix. The room is quiet except for the hiss of venting steam and the faint, rhythmic clicking of a single Spider Worker trying to fix a machine that will never run again.
THE HANDOFF (The Final Test)
Read Aloud:
"Varon steps back from the wreckage. He holds the Aetherial Matrix in his right hand. It is the size of a human heart, geometric and flawless, pulsing with a harsh, angry amber light. The moment it cleared the brass housing, the air in the workshop changed. It feels heavy, tasting of copper and ozone. A deep, sickening vibration starts in your teeth.
The Matrix is an unshielded power core. It is leaking raw tonal radiation. Varon’s Breton-mask doesn't slip, but he grimaces slightly, shifting his grip as if the crystal is vibrating uncomfortably against his palm.
He looks across the room at Kyboh. He doesn't say a word. He just holds it out, waiting."
THE PAUSE (The Spotlight)
(Stop talking. Look directly at Kyboh’s player.)
GM: "Kyboh, the immediate threat is dead. The object you abandoned the surface world to find—the core Hjolmar needs to rebuild your hands—is ten feet away from you. The air in the room is thick with its power.
Before you take it from Varon... before anyone takes another step toward the exit... I am going to ask you: Is there anything specific you want to do? Is there anything you need to prepare?"
THE RESOLUTION (The Two Paths)
Path A: The Miracle (He Remembers the Anchor)
If he says: "I need to put on the Anchor of Stasis before I touch that thing."
The Result: He secures the heavy lead collar around his neck. The psychic static in his head vanishes. The ambient hum of the Matrix is instantly muffled to him. He can safely take the core from Varon. The party breathes a sigh of relief. You proceed directly to THE TRIGGER (The Alarm) below.
Path B: The Inevitable (He Forgets/Ignores It)
If he says: "I take it," or "No, I'm good," or is otherwise distracted.
The Execution: Do not prompt him again. You gave him the spotlight and the warning. Proceed immediately to THE CORE BREACH.

THE CORE BREACH (Kyboh's Consequence)
(Triggered only if Kyboh takes the Matrix without the Anchor of Stasis)
Read Aloud (Coldly and clinically):
"You walk over to Varon. You reach out your bare hands—the hands whose bones are enchanted with a fractured, unstable tonal matrix. You are not wearing the Anchor. Your skeleton is 'live.'
The moment your fingers touch the Aetherial crystal, the world goes white.
It is not a sound. It is a physical impact. The Matrix is designed to stabilize a harmonic frequency; it grabs hold of the chaotic, doubling enchantment in your marrow and tries to force it into a perfect loop. But there is no ceramic housing to absorb the force. There is no gauntlet to channel it. There is only your flesh.
You feel the Titan's Tithe activate. One point of force. Then two. Then four. Then eight. It cycles exponentially in the space of a heartbeat. A shockwave of pure, invisible kinetic force explodes outward from your hands."
The Mechanical Resolution:
The Mutation (Kyboh's Agony):
Mechanic: Kyboh does not get a save. The energy surges up his arms. He takes 15 Irreducible Damage.
The Visual: The grey, ceramic-like skin on his hands and forearms fractures violently. Jagged, smoking bone spurs tear through the skin at his knuckles, wrists, and elbows. He screams as his skeleton forcibly expands to contain the pressure.
The Permanent Debuff (Ossification Cascade): His Unarmed strikes now deal +2 Damage and Bleed, but switching weapons or using items now requires a Major Action due to locked, agonizing joints. He must now perform the nightly "grinding" ritual or lose his multi-attacks.


The Blast (Party Damage):
Mechanic: Every creature within 15 feet of Kyboh must make a Hard (-4) Might Save.
Failure: They take 10 Irreducible Force Damage and are knocked Prone, blood running from their noses from the sheer acoustic pressure.
Success: They take 5 damage and stay standing.


GEAR’s Warning:
GEAR rights himself, his lens clicking frantically. "Warning! Unregulated tonal feedback detected! Primary Organic Designate Kyboh's skeletal resonance is engaging in an uncontrolled amplification cycle with the Matrix! Recommend immediate suppression or the biological vessel will undergo terminal structural detonation within 180 seconds!"


The Panic:
Kyboh drops the Matrix. His hands are bleeding, bone jutting through his skin. The Matrix sits on the floor, radiating a teeth-rattling hum. He must put the Anchor of Stasis on now.
Once the Anchor is finally secured (requiring a frantic, painful scramble), the room goes dead silent. The psychic static stops. The Matrix can be handled safely.
(Pause. Let the dust settle. Then proceed to the Alarm.)

THE TRIGGER (The Alarm)
Location: The threshold between the Workshop and the Cognitorium staircase.
Trigger: The first character (likely Kyboh carrying the Matrix, or someone fleeing the explosion) crosses the threshold back into the staircase.
Read Aloud:
"You step back through the doorway, intending to begin the long climb out.
The amber lamps snap to crimson.
Every light in the sphere—the archive, the staircase, the corridors—flashes from warm gold to a harsh, pulsing red. A new sound builds in the walls. Not an explosion. A TONE. A sustained, grinding, high-frequency vibration that you feel in the roots of your teeth and the bones of your jaw. Every bronze pipe in the Cognitorium is screaming the exact same note.
Above you, in the walls and the ceiling, you hear the sound of heavy locks disengaging. Dozens of them. Simultaneously.
GEAR spins, his amber eye clicking rapidly between red and gold.
'Safe Integration Protocol has been terminated. System-wide biological purge activated. All non-authorized organic material will be eradicated.'
He pauses, looking at you.
'That would be you. Current survival probability: 4.2%. I recommend we leave immediately.'"
👁️ DAVINIA SEES:
Through the Wizard Eyes, the entire Cognitorium shifts from dormant, sleeping blue leylines to a violent, thrashing web of angry red intent. The city isn't defending itself; it is cleaning an infection. Every wall, every pipe, every surface is lit with a single, unified directive: EXTIRPATE.
