ESCAPE PHASE 4: THE SURFACE LIFT
Location: Central transit hub. The Surface Lift platform. The four brass resonator tubes.
THE ROOM (Read Aloud)
"The transit hub opens — widest space in the city, corridors converging. The Surface Lift platform sits in the center. The four brass tubes at the cardinal points, exactly as you left them.
Behind you, the swarm filling the corridor. Ahead, the platform. Four notes played in the right order while the flood closes in."
THE SPLIT
Defenders (2+ characters): Hold the corridor entrance. Chokepoint is 15 feet wide. Might TN 14 each round to hold the line. Failure: swarm breaks through, everyone on the platform takes 5 Shock + 4 FP drain.
Activator (1 character): Play four tubes in sequence. One tube per round. 4 rounds total. No check if they remember the sequence (W → N → S → E). If forgotten: Guile TN 10 to recall.
Support: Assist defenders (grants Advantage), heal, area abilities.
GEAR at the chokepoint: Tonal Pulse concentrates perfectly in the 15-foot corridor mouth. Every spider in range staggered for a full round. One use. Make it count.
THE ACTIVATION
Tube 1 (West): Gears engage. Grinding from below.
Tube 2 (North): Platform jolts. Vibrates.
Tube 3 (South): Mechanism locks. Platform lifts one inch off housing.
Tube 4 (East): Emergency ascent. The lift LAUNCHES upward — violent acceleration that throws everyone off their feet. Not the smooth descent. A catapult.
"The platform rockets upward. The transit hub drops away. Bronze walls blur past. The tonal alarm fades from scream to hum to nothing.
The platform SLAMS into its surface housing. Gears lock. Bronze doors spiral open.
Cold air. Snow. Wind."

You are absolutely right. I completely missed the mark by trying to compress it. If they spent 3 sessions creeping down into this place, the escape shouldn't be a montage—it should be a grueling, room-by-room, floor-by-floor fight for their lives where they feel the agonizing distance of every single step they took to get down there.
And regarding the DR: If their DR is capping at 20-25, a 15-damage hit is literally nothing. The baseline failure damage needs to be 40+ Physical or 30+ Shock/Magic just to make them bleed.
Here is the fully expanded, room-by-room gauntlet. We are doing this exactly as you demanded: High volume of rolls, every single room revisited, the 8-phase Deep Lift, and the 2-phase Surface Lift.
THE MECHANIC: THE TOLL OF 8
In every single Zone/Phase, the party needs 8 Safe Passages (5 PCs, Varon, Ylva, GEAR).
Players can roll for themselves.
Players can take on multiple rolls to cover the NPCs or weaker party members (e.g., "I'm rolling Might to bash a path, and Agility to drag Varon through it." = 2 Rolls = 2 Safe Passages).
Every missed roll = One catastrophic hit. If a player fails a roll meant to protect an NPC, the player takes the hit for them.
THE DAMAGE PROFILES (Adjusted for 20-25 DR)
When a roll fails, hit them with one of these depending on the fiction of how they failed:
The Meat Grinder (Physical): 45 Physical Damage. (Even at 25 DR, they lose 20 HP).
The Tonal Overload (Shock): 30 Shock Damage + 15 FP Drain.
The Crush (Environmental): 35 Bludgeoning Damage + Staggered (Lose next Major Action).

PART 1: THE COGNITORIUM ASCENT
